               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> (amh.) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> pauper </quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> egenus </quote>
                        </cit> (<lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> Lud. <lbl expand="lexicon">lex.</lbl> amh. <lbl expand="columna">col.</lbl> 79): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንባቦ፡ ለነዳይ፡ ወግዩር፡ ወዜጋ፡ አስተቃለልኩ፡ ወንባበ፡ ባዕል፡ አልዐልኩ፡</foreign> Form. Conf. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain">
                        <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>zegā</quote>
                        </cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>subject</quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>a person who has to pay tribute</quote>
                        </cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይኩን፡ ዮም፡ ጕዕዞ፡ እስመ፡ ይፈቅዱ፡ ጨዋ፡ ተመይጦተ፡ መንገለል፡ ሸዋ፡ ከመ፡ ያጥፍኡ፡ ዜጋ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                            <quote>“Il faut se mettre en marche aujourd‘hui, car les Č̣awā désirent retourner au Schoa pour ruiner les contribuables”</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
